On October 26, 2020, President Trump delivered remarks at the White House to mark the swearing-in of Justice Amy Coney Barrett as a Supreme Court justice. He praised Barrett's credentials and emphasized her commitment to ruling based on a faithful reading of the law and the Constitution. President Trump also expressed gratitude to Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell and Senate Judiciary Chairman Lindsey Graham for their support in the confirmation process. Justice Barrett, in her remarks, thanked President Trump for selecting her and expressed her dedication to upholding the Constitution and the rule of law. She highlighted the importance of judicial independence and the duty of judges to resist their own policy preferences.